parameters.Good: 2: The network quality is quite good, but the bitrate may be slightly lower than excellent.

parameters.Poor: 3: Users can feel the communication slightly impaired.

parameters.VBad: 5: The quality is so bad that users can barely communicate.

parameters.Down: 6: The network is down and users cannot communicate at all.

parameters.Unsupported: 7: Users cannot detect the network quality. (Not in use.)
